1
00:00:14,360 --> 00:00:17,440
♪In the airport lounge
at the break of day♪

2
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:22,240
♪A page of dust beneath my fingers♪

3
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:25,160
♪Filled with stories♪

4
00:00:25,160 --> 00:00:28,280
♪That others never got to tell♪

5
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,960
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

6
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:35,600
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

7
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,160
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

8
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:40,040
♪The world is split an inch wider♪

9
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,600
♪Raise your eyes, face the light♪

10
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:45,080
♪See the truth, and see the fright♪

11
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,800
♪Guard the crack within this door♪

12
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:52,600
♪Keep the way back home
always burning bright♪

13
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:57,040
♪The camera pans
across the boarding crowd♪

14
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:59,200
♪Some wear a smile,
some have their eyes adrift♪

15
00:00:59,280 --> 00:01:01,440
♪A red suitcase♪

16
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:05,360
♪Tied with faded pasts
and broken prayers♪

17
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:09,400
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

18
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:12,080
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

19
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:13,960
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

20
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:17,400
♪It's the heartbeat
echoing the call of law♪

21
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,000
[Gimlet Eyes]

22
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:33,000
[Episode 18]

23
00:01:34,720 --> 00:01:35,760
Besides Chen Wei,

24
00:01:36,440 --> 00:01:37,680
who else has contacted you?

25
00:01:39,640 --> 00:01:40,320
No one else.

26
00:01:41,440 --> 00:01:42,760
What about the doll in the restroom?

27
00:01:43,040 --> 00:01:44,000
Did that have anything to do with you?

28
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:45,280
No.

29
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:47,200
Could Chen Wei have put it there?

30
00:01:48,360 --> 00:01:49,440
Probably not.

31
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:53,880
They wouldn't take that risk.

32
00:01:54,520 --> 00:01:55,600
If they were

33
00:01:55,960 --> 00:01:57,200
behind it,

34
00:01:57,680 --> 00:01:58,720
they would've come to me.

35
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:07,600
Mr. Guo asked me to get you a hot meal.

36
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:22,960
Liu.

37
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:28,080
When the anti-smuggling unit
questions you,

38
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:30,160
tell them everything straight.

39
00:02:33,920 --> 00:02:34,360
I understand.

40
00:02:36,960 --> 00:02:37,520
I'm off.

41
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:52,400
Chen Wei.

42
00:02:53,720 --> 00:02:54,920
We need you
to cooperate with an investigation.

43
00:02:54,920 --> 00:02:55,920
Come with us.

44
00:03:01,760 --> 00:03:05,200
[Customs Dormitory]

45
00:03:22,760 --> 00:03:23,840
Does it hurt?

46
00:03:24,720 --> 00:03:25,760
Not at all. I'm fine.

47
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:27,240
Don't play tough.

48
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:29,240
A full cup of boiling water
right to your chest.

49
00:03:29,320 --> 00:03:30,320
Of course it hurts.

50
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:32,840
Don't worry.

51
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:34,760
By the time the water hit me,

52
00:03:34,760 --> 00:03:36,760
it had already cooled down by 10%.

53
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:39,080
And my uniform blocked
and absorbed a lot of the heat.

54
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:40,440
The only part that really hurt

55
00:03:40,440 --> 00:03:41,920
was that first second.

56
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:43,640
It's been hours already.

57
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:44,800
I'm totally fine now.

58
00:03:44,840 --> 00:03:46,640
Then why did you
step in front of me like that?

59
00:03:48,440 --> 00:03:49,640
I don't know.

60
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:51,160
My body just reacted on its own.

61
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:56,720
Yu.

62
00:03:56,840 --> 00:03:58,840
I don't think
you have any burn cream here.

63
00:03:58,840 --> 00:04:00,000
I'll go grab some.

64
00:04:36,240 --> 00:04:37,720
When are you going to tell her?

65
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:41,600
Tell her what?

66
00:04:42,240 --> 00:04:43,600
There are three things in life

67
00:04:43,640 --> 00:04:45,640
you just can't hide.

68
00:04:47,280 --> 00:04:47,920
Cough.

69
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:49,080
Love.

70
00:04:52,640 --> 00:04:54,040
You've already got two out of three.

71
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:55,800
Have I?

72
00:04:57,080 --> 00:04:58,600
You think all our people-reading skills

73
00:04:58,640 --> 00:05:00,360
were for nothing?

74
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:03,600
What are you so nervous about?

75
00:05:05,720 --> 00:05:07,080
If you like her,

76
00:05:07,280 --> 00:05:08,920
just be brave and tell her.

77
00:05:09,520 --> 00:05:10,880
I do think

78
00:05:11,080 --> 00:05:12,280
Xiaoyan is great.

79
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:15,520
I just don't know
how she feels about me.

80
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:20,960
You know what?

81
00:05:21,520 --> 00:05:22,400
The moment a woman

82
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:25,080
starts worrying about a man,

83
00:05:25,760 --> 00:05:27,000
she's already fallen for him.

84
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:30,720
This.

85
00:05:32,280 --> 00:05:33,560
What a perfect chance.

86
00:05:34,280 --> 00:05:35,480
Don't let it slip by.

87
00:05:36,960 --> 00:05:37,320
But

88
00:05:37,320 --> 00:05:38,360
I really do think

89
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:39,960
this injury isn't a big deal.

90
00:05:39,960 --> 00:05:42,520
I think it's perfectly fine
if you say it is.

91
00:05:44,840 --> 00:05:46,040
Got the medicine.

92
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:50,560
Lyu Xiaoyan,

93
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:52,760
it's not like he's dying.

94
00:05:52,880 --> 00:05:54,080
What's the rush?

95
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:55,320
He got hurt because of me.

96
00:05:55,320 --> 00:05:56,680
I have to take responsibility.

97
00:05:57,960 --> 00:05:59,200
She's ready
to take responsibility for you.

98
00:05:59,200 --> 00:06:00,440
Don't mess this up.

99
00:06:00,520 --> 00:06:01,160
Yu!

100
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:02,400
What are you saying?

101
00:06:04,600 --> 00:06:05,320
Nothing.

102
00:06:06,320 --> 00:06:07,360
I'm off

103
00:06:07,640 --> 00:06:08,920
to practice my people-reading skills.

104
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:11,160
See ya.

105
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:20,000
Then let me

106
00:06:20,760 --> 00:06:21,680
put the cream on for you.

107
00:06:26,840 --> 00:06:27,680
No, no, it's fine.

108
00:06:27,760 --> 00:06:28,040
I can

109
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:28,960
do it myself.

110
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:29,520
Don't bother.

111
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,000
Yan Bowen,

112
00:06:31,320 --> 00:06:32,640
I already saw everything earlier.

113
00:06:32,640 --> 00:06:33,960
And now you're getting shy?

114
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:35,400
Too late.

115
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:37,280
Lyu Xiaoyan, you…

116
00:06:38,320 --> 00:06:39,160
Hurry up.

117
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:41,680
Please, like I even wanted to look.

118
00:06:41,880 --> 00:06:42,400
Lift your shirt.

119
00:06:47,840 --> 00:06:48,520
Putting it on now.

120
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:54,400
That post

121
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:56,200
you made on Weibo before,

122
00:06:56,200 --> 00:06:56,920
did you mean it?

123
00:06:57,840 --> 00:06:59,480
I post a lot on Weibo.

124
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:00,480
Which one?

125
00:07:01,080 --> 00:07:03,080
February 13th of last year,

126
00:07:03,280 --> 00:07:04,880
10:13 PM.

127
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:09,640
You even remember the exact time?

128
00:07:10,440 --> 00:07:12,400
"Does every girl have her own hero?"

129
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:12,800
Question mark.

130
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:13,840
"And if so,

131
00:07:13,840 --> 00:07:15,000
I'd like to ask mine,

132
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:16,440
are you

133
00:07:16,440 --> 00:07:17,160
running late?"

134
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:17,680
Question mark.

135
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:18,880
"If you can't find the way,

136
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:20,360
I can be your GPS…"

137
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:21,360
Look,

138
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:22,840
everyone has weak moments.

139
00:07:22,840 --> 00:07:24,720
I just wasn't thinking straight.

140
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:26,320
I don't even know what I was thinking.

141
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:30,160
Can I be that person?

142
00:07:35,520 --> 00:07:36,560
Be what?

143
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:40,360
I'm no hero,

144
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:42,240
but I'm right here for you.

145
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:44,520
And I'll stay right here.

146
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:46,560
Always.

147
00:07:51,280 --> 00:07:53,240
So that's what you meant.

148
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:53,760
Okay.

149
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:54,680
Well,

150
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,160
let's give it a shot then.

151
00:07:56,160 --> 00:07:57,720
We were pretty in sync

152
00:07:57,720 --> 00:07:58,800
when we pretended to be a couple.

153
00:07:58,840 --> 00:08:00,520
And back then you were…

154
00:08:02,960 --> 00:08:03,600
Really…

155
00:08:05,840 --> 00:08:06,960
I'm serious.

156
00:08:09,160 --> 00:08:10,640
Alright then,

157
00:08:10,720 --> 00:08:12,040
this is your probation period.

158
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:13,320
Do well,
and maybe I'll make it official.

159
00:08:15,520 --> 00:08:16,120
Deal.

160
00:08:17,840 --> 00:08:18,920
Oh, and don't let

161
00:08:18,920 --> 00:08:20,480
Shihuo and Dayu find out.

162
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:21,760
They're way too nosy.

163
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:23,120
Are you sure

164
00:08:23,520 --> 00:08:24,800
we can really pull off

165
00:08:24,840 --> 00:08:26,080
the 'we're not close' act
in front of them?

166
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:29,600
Well,

167
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:32,120
anyway,

168
00:08:32,280 --> 00:08:33,240
just

169
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:35,240
don't let them know.

170
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:37,280
Let's keep this between us for now.

171
00:08:37,920 --> 00:08:38,800
We can

172
00:08:40,240 --> 00:08:41,120
take it slow.

173
00:08:48,320 --> 00:08:49,280
Hey, what are you doing?

174
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:52,720
I…

175
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:55,280
Weren't you putting
the burn cream on me?

176
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:57,720
After all that,
you only wiped it with water?

177
00:08:57,760 --> 00:08:58,720
W-where's the cream?

178
00:09:01,680 --> 00:09:02,200
I forgot.

179
00:09:02,440 --> 00:09:03,120
It's your fault.

180
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:04,080
I…

181
00:09:04,520 --> 00:09:06,240
Do it yourself. I've got stuff to do.

182
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:07,200
I'm very busy.

183
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:10,080
You just said you'd take responsibility.

184
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:11,560
Does that still count?

185
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:13,360
Yes.

186
00:09:25,520 --> 00:09:26,040
Li.

187
00:09:27,720 --> 00:09:29,080
You need to make a decision.

188
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:32,600
Dabao.

189
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:34,360
I know

190
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:36,240
you've never liked Ken.

191
00:09:37,920 --> 00:09:40,080
But he's always been loyal to me.

192
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:42,360
Li,

193
00:09:43,320 --> 00:09:44,920
whether I like him or not

194
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:46,800
has nothing to do with it.

195
00:09:47,640 --> 00:09:49,400
Layers of Mountains
got seized by Customs.

196
00:09:49,760 --> 00:09:51,560
Chen Wei will give him up in no time.

197
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:53,320
Once he gets arrested,

198
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:55,720
I don't buy that he'd stay loyal.

199
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:56,760
So,

200
00:09:57,400 --> 00:09:58,520
he has to go.

201
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:00,720
There's really no other way?

202
00:10:02,480 --> 00:10:03,000
Li,

203
00:10:03,680 --> 00:10:05,040
think about what Mr. E always says.

204
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:06,720
Cut off an arm to save your life.

205
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:17,360
Do it.

206
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:14,600
Dabao.

207
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:17,760
What the hell is this place?

208
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:21,000
This is supposed to be a hotel.

209
00:11:21,040 --> 00:11:22,400
Speak Chinese.

210
00:11:23,800 --> 00:11:24,520
I mean,

211
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:26,920
what on earth is this place?

212
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:28,680
It's terrible here.

213
00:11:29,520 --> 00:11:31,080
It'll be fine once you're inside.

214
00:11:32,160 --> 00:11:33,000
Where?

215
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:33,760
Right here.

216
00:11:44,320 --> 00:11:45,120
Dabao.

217
00:11:46,120 --> 00:11:47,520
Nobody can stay here.

218
00:11:48,720 --> 00:11:50,480
Do you even know

219
00:11:51,040 --> 00:11:51,920
what's going on right now?

220
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:53,840
What, you expect me
to take you to a hotel?

221
00:11:54,040 --> 00:11:55,040
No.

222
00:11:55,320 --> 00:11:57,880
You know how fast I had to get out.

223
00:11:58,120 --> 00:11:59,800
All I grabbed was cash. Nothing else.

224
00:12:00,240 --> 00:12:01,160
No worries.

225
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:03,280
I'll go get you what you need.

226
00:12:05,640 --> 00:12:07,560
You know
I haven't had dinner yet, right?

227
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:13,920
Damn Long Shuo and Chen Wei.

228
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:16,440
What?

229
00:12:17,320 --> 00:12:19,520
You're trying to drag me down with you?

230
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:22,040
I'm sick of all this.

231
00:13:28,040 --> 00:13:28,760
Dabao.

232
00:13:30,120 --> 00:13:31,040
About the money,

233
00:13:31,880 --> 00:13:32,760
I don't need it anymore.

234
00:13:32,960 --> 00:13:33,880
You keep it.

235
00:13:34,960 --> 00:13:35,760
Thank you.

236
00:13:37,560 --> 00:13:38,840
Ken's gone now.

237
00:13:39,640 --> 00:13:40,760
From now on,

238
00:13:41,240 --> 00:13:42,680
you're the only one I can count on.

239
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:46,640
Don't worry, Li.

240
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:48,800
Even if
the whole world turns against you,

241
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:49,960
I never will.

242
00:13:52,680 --> 00:13:54,440
This really hit us hard.

243
00:13:56,040 --> 00:13:57,880
Gotta rebuild our overseas network
from scratch.

244
00:13:58,560 --> 00:13:59,360
It's okay.

245
00:14:00,160 --> 00:14:01,560
If it comes to that,
I can sign up for classes

246
00:14:01,720 --> 00:14:02,920
and learn some English.

247
00:14:05,880 --> 00:14:07,040
Just knowing you'd do that

248
00:14:07,360 --> 00:14:08,480
is enough for me.

249
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:15,480
Li,

250
00:14:16,280 --> 00:14:17,480
there's something I want to say.

251
00:14:17,880 --> 00:14:18,680
Go ahead.

252
00:14:19,680 --> 00:14:21,240
I think this Mr. E

253
00:14:22,240 --> 00:14:23,320
is a real piece of trash.

254
00:14:24,480 --> 00:14:25,800
If he'd told us from the start

255
00:14:26,280 --> 00:14:27,880
about what Long Shuo and Chen Wei

256
00:14:27,880 --> 00:14:28,680
were up to,

257
00:14:28,840 --> 00:14:30,400
we wouldn't be in this mess.

258
00:14:30,920 --> 00:14:32,320
We lost people,

259
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:34,160
and that painting worth a fortune.

260
00:14:35,640 --> 00:14:36,680
I honestly feel like

261
00:14:36,680 --> 00:14:38,840
Mr. E has never once looked out for us.

262
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:41,360
Of course I know that.

263
00:14:42,920 --> 00:14:43,720
But

264
00:14:43,760 --> 00:14:45,440
we dropped the ball first.

265
00:14:45,800 --> 00:14:47,080
We can't blame all of this on him.

266
00:14:50,040 --> 00:14:50,680
Li,

267
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:53,080
who exactly

268
00:14:53,520 --> 00:14:55,120
is this Mr. E?

269
00:14:55,520 --> 00:14:56,840
You've never told me anything.

270
00:14:57,160 --> 00:14:57,760
Well,

271
00:14:58,080 --> 00:14:59,680
he's always kept himself hidden.

272
00:15:03,560 --> 00:15:04,960
After these three years,

273
00:15:06,520 --> 00:15:07,840
my impression of him is that

274
00:15:08,040 --> 00:15:09,200
he's extremely calculating

275
00:15:09,760 --> 00:15:11,120
and absolutely ruthless.

276
00:15:11,920 --> 00:15:14,520
He doesn't even care
how our business is doing.

277
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:16,840
All he cares about is finding mules.

278
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:18,960
He's an expert at manipulating people.

279
00:15:21,520 --> 00:15:22,400
And that

280
00:15:22,680 --> 00:15:24,040
is exactly what scares me the most.

281
00:15:25,560 --> 00:15:27,440
Standing in front of him,

282
00:15:28,240 --> 00:15:29,480
I feel completely exposed,

283
00:15:29,480 --> 00:15:30,440
like I have nowhere to hide.

284
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:31,800
So,

285
00:15:32,880 --> 00:15:34,600
we're just supposed to
let him hide in the shadows

286
00:15:34,720 --> 00:15:36,760
and keep doing whatever he says?

287
00:15:37,480 --> 00:15:38,880
I used to hold back

288
00:15:38,880 --> 00:15:40,640
because of how he took down Sa Ziyi.

289
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:41,560
So

290
